HEADWORD: Tunable
<hw>Tun"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Capable of being
tuned, or made harmonious; hence, harmonious; musical; tuneful.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Tun"a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> -- <wf>Tun"a*bly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>tunable</qex> as sylvan pipe or song.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tun-bellied</ent>⟦br⟧
